http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 25 Jul 2019
Source: OIE, WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System), weekly disease information 2019 [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=31188


Equine infectious anemia, Peru
------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 25 Jul 2019 from Dr. Mercedes Lucia Flores Cancino, [Veterinary Doctor], Animal Health Directorate, Agricultural Health Service, Lima, Peru

Summary
Report type: Immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 5 Jul 2019
Date of confirmation of the event: 11 Jul 2019
Report date: 25 Jul 2019
Date submitted to OIE: 25 Jul 2019
Reason for notification: Recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 6 May 2019
Manifestation of disease: Sub-clinical infection
Causal agent: Equine infectious anemia virus [EIAV]
Nature of diagnosis: Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to the whole country.

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1: San Isidro de Chilina, Inapari, Tahuamanu, [Madre de Dios]
Date of start of the outbreak: 5 Jul 2019
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Equidae / 14 / 9 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Animals used for field work

Outbreak 2: San Isidro de Chilina, Inapari, Tahuamanu, [Madre de Dios]
Date of start of the outbreak: 15 Jul 2019
Outbreak status: Continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: Farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Equidae / 5 / 3 / 0 / 0 / 0
Affected population: Animals used for field work

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Equidae / 19 / 12 / 0 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]:
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Equidae / 63.16 / 0 / 0 / 0
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: Unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: Sampling was carried out in the surveillance zone on 17 equids in 3 holdings, and 3 equids tested positive on the AGID test; the affected holding was notified as the 2nd outbreak. In addition, other animals in contact with the 1st outbreak were tested: 7 equids in 2 premises were sampled, and all gave negative results on the AGID test. The distance between the outbreaks and the city of Lima is about 760 km (about 472 mi) in a straight line.

Control measures
Measures applied: Movement control inside the country; surveillance outside containment and/or protection zone; surveillance within containment and/or protection zone; quarantine; disinfection; control of vectors; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals.
Measures to be applied: Selective killing and disposal

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Animal Health Diagnostic Center Unit (national laboratory) / Equidae / Agar-gel immunodiffusion (AGID) / 11 Jul 2019 / Positive
Animal Health Diagnostic Center Unit (national laboratory) / Equidae / Agar-gel immunodiffusion (AGID) / 22 Jul 2019 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

